As you progress through Snapshot youÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ll use the camera in new and interesting ways, like taking photographs of light and using it to interact with physics. Your camera even captures an objectÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s momentum. This, combined with the ability to rotate photographs as you paste them, leads to more complex and interesting gameplay. For example, if a snowball is falling when you snap a photo, the snowball will hurl upwards if you paste that photograph back into the world upside-down. You can even use this to take photographs of enemy projectiles and aim them right back at them! 
